To write a function that checks for prime numbers in an array of numbers, you can use a helper function called `isPrime()`. This function will take a single number and check if it is prime.

Here's an example implementation of the `primeChecker()` function in JavaScript:
```javascript
function isPrime(num) {
  if (num < 2) return false;
  if (num == 2) return true;
  if (num % 2 == 0) return false;
  for (let i = 3; i * i <= num; i += 2) {
    if (num % i == 0) return false;
  }
  return true;
}

function primeChecker(arr) {
  arr.forEach((num) => {
    if (isPrime(num)) console.log(num);
  });
}
```
