In the above code, we have a `chat-container` that holds the chatbot interface, a `chat-header` that contains the chatbot title, a `chat-body` that holds the chat area and the input container, and a `chat-area` that contains the chat history and the user input. The `chat-history-modal` is where the chat history from the modal will be displayed.

Now, let's create a JavaScript file to add functionality to the chatbot.

JavaScript:
```javascript
// Get modal and its elements
const chatModal = document.getElementById('chat-modal');
const modalContent = document.querySelector('.modal-content');
const chatHistoryModal = document.querySelector('.chat-history-modal');
const closeButton = document.querySelector('.close');

// Get elements in the chat container
const chatHistory = document.querySelector('.chat-history');
const userInput = document.getElementById('user-input');
const sendButton = document.getElementById('send-button');

// Function to create and append chat message elements
const appendMessage = (message, className) => {
    const messageElement = document.createElement('div');
    messageElement.classList.add(className);
    messageElement.innerText = message;
    return messageElement;
}

// Function to toggle the modal
